cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GR

The paper discusses the use of Theano framework for implementing complex differential geometry algorithms and non-linear statistics for modeling deformation of anatomical shapes. This involves handling high-dimensional data structures and performing fast computations on them. Based on this, the most likely sub-category is computer vision (cs.CV) as it involves analyzing and modeling anatomical shapes. The next likely sub-categories are machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as they deal with non-linear statistics and complex algorithms. Neural networks (cs.NE) is also a likely sub-category as it involves handling high-dimensional data structures. Finally, graphics (cs.GR) is a possible sub-category as the paper discusses visualizing the implemented theory on landmark representations of Corpus Callosum shapes.
